---
layout: layouts/base.njk
description: I help new web developers build great websites on their own without going through tutorial hell and experiencing the blank page syndrome.
numberOfBestBlogsToShow: 6
numberOfLatestBlogsToShow: 4
copyright:
  year: 2024, 2025, 2026
---

{% include "header/full.njk" %}
<main tabindex="-1">
  <div class="hero prose" data-prose-align="start">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="wrapper" data-wrapper-type="inner">
        <div class="flow">
          <h1>Go <em>again</em></h1>
          <p class="hero__description prose__article">
            I help new web developers build great websites on their own without
            going through tutorial hell and experiencing the blank page
            syndrome.
          </p>
          <div class="cluster">
            <a
              href="/smart-website/"
              class="button"
              data-button-variant="light"
            >
              Smart Website
              <svg
                width="24"
                height="24"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                aria-hidden="true"
                focusable="false"
              >
                <g fill="currentColor">
                  <use href="#arrow-up-right"></use>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </a>
            <a href="/blog/" class="button">
              View all articles
              <svg
                width="24"
                height="24"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                aria-hidden="true"
                focusable="false"
              >
                <g fill="currentColor">
                  <use href="#arrow-up-right"></use>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="magic">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="wrapper" data-wrapper-type="inner">
        <p><span>One birth, one life, one death</span></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="promo">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="wrapper" data-wrapper-type="inner">
        <div class="flow flow-space-m-l">
          <h2>Who I am</h2>
          <ul role="list" class="grid">
            <li class="box">
              <h3>Speak my mind without being politically correct</h3>
              <p>
                I am not afraid of being hated by so many people. In fact, if I
                hurt your feelings, that is my pleasure. I want to be
                honest, and I need to pay the price. Think of my writings like
                this: "Why does this guy write like this?" Wrong is wrong. Let's
                learn to say things as is!
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="box">
              <h3>Accessibility is more important than beauty</h3>
              <p>
                Doing better job does not always mean developing spectacular
                design. I prefer
                <a href="/blog/redesigning-proving/">simple interfaces</a> over
                complicated ones. If a website is elegant but people are
                struggling to use it, it is just garbage.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="box">
              <h3>Write about real problems with real solutions</h3>
              <p>
                We want to live in a better world. But the current world is bad.
                <a href="/blog/personal-websites-suicide-transgender/"
                  >It has lots of problems</a
                >. I write about them. I ensure that my articles give solutions.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="box">
              <h3>Christianity is what I believe and what I preach</h3>
              <p>
                The content on this website is influenced by Christ's teachings,
                for sure. I am a <a href="/beliefs/">Christian</a>. While I am
                still alive, I want to help people with my skills at the maximum
                level.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="articles" data-articles-page="home" data-articles-type="best">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="wrapper" data-wrapper-type="inner">
        <div class="flow box">
          <h2 class="articles__headline">Best articles</h2>
          <p class="articles__lede">
            Why do you think I am going to be what others want? Or why do you
            think I am the same as others?
          </p>
        </div>
        {% set blogList = collections.best | blogSliceFilter(-1 *
        numberOfBestBlogsToShow) %}
        <ul class="articles__list grid" role="list">
          {% for blog in blogList | reverse %}
          <li class="articles__item box cluster">
            <div class="flow flow-space-2xs">
              <p>
                <span class="articles__author"
                  >{{ blog.data.author.name }}</span
                >
                <em>wrote</em>
              </p>
              <h3 class="articles__title">
                <a href="{{ blog.url }}"
                  >{{ blog.data.title | titleCaseFilter }}</a
                >
              </h3>
              {% set publishedDate = blog.date %}
              <p>
                <time datetime="{{ publishedDate | htmlDateFilter }}"
                  >{{ publishedDate | blogDateFilter }}</time
                >
              </p>
              {% if blog.data.description %} {% markdown %}{{
              blog.data.description }}{% endmarkdown %} {% endif %}
            </div>
            <p>
              {% set category = blog.data.tags[1] %} {% set tagUrl
              %}/category/{{ category | slugify }}/{% endset %}
              <a href="{{ tagUrl }}" class="badge">{{ category }}</a>
            </p>
          </li>
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="articles" data-articles-page="home">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="wrapper" data-wrapper-type="inner">
        <div class="flow box">
          <h2 class="articles__headline">Latest articles</h2>
          <p class="articles__lede">
            I am now interested in web accessibility, writing in plain language,
            understanding the mind, and static site generators.
          </p>
          <p>
            <a href="/blog/" class="button" data-button-variant="light">
              View all articles
              <svg
                width="24"
                height="24"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                aria-hidden="true"
                focusable="false"
              >
                <g fill="currentColor">
                  <use href="#arrow-up-right"></use>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
        {% set blogList = collections.latest | blogSliceFilter(-1 *
        numberOfLatestBlogsToShow) %}
        <ol class="articles__list grid" role="list" reversed>
          {% include "blog/list.njk" %}
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="topics">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="wrapper" data-wrapper-type="inner">
        <div class="sidebar">
          <h2>Topics</h2>
          {% set tags = collections.sort %} {% include "blog/categories.njk" %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="motivation">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="wrapper" data-wrapper-type="inner">
        <div class="flow">
          <h2 class="badge" data-badge-variant="transparent">Motivation</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>My people are destroyed for lack of knowledge…</strong>
          </p>
          <p>—Hosea 4:6, King James Version</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>
{% include "footer.njk" %}
